<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="599" pageId="5" pageNumber="598" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1585,2006]" box="[151,692,1585,1610]" pageId="5" pageNumber="598">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,322,1585,1610]" pageId="5" pageNumber="598">Measurement.</emphasis>
Male, 2.7mm (including wings).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1585,2006]" pageId="5" pageNumber="598">
Dorsum light brownish-write with two brownish-yellow bands extending from anterior margin of vertex to end of pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[306,382,1657,1682]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–16" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1892,1914]" captionTargetBox="[186,1384,299,1846]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,265,1871]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–16. Habitus (dorsal view and lateral view), crown, pronotum and scutellum (dorsal view), and face. 1, 5, 9, 13, T. quadripunctata Thapa &amp; Sohi, 1986 rec. nov.; 2, 6, 10, 14, T. eleganta sp. nov.; 3, 7, 11, 15, T. robusta sp. nov.; 4, 8, 12, 16, T. elongata sp. nov. Scale. 1–8, 0.5mm; 9–10, 0.2mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1455373/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="598">Fig.12</figureCitation>
); face brownish-yellow (
<figureCitation box="[662,738,1657,1682]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–16" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1892,1914]" captionTargetBox="[186,1384,299,1846]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,265,1871]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–16. Habitus (dorsal view and lateral view), crown, pronotum and scutellum (dorsal view), and face. 1, 5, 9, 13, T. quadripunctata Thapa &amp; Sohi, 1986 rec. nov.; 2, 6, 10, 14, T. eleganta sp. nov.; 3, 7, 11, 15, T. robusta sp. nov.; 4, 8, 12, 16, T. elongata sp. nov. Scale. 1–8, 0.5mm; 9–10, 0.2mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1455373/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="598">Fig.16</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1585,2006]" pageId="5" pageNumber="598">
Abdominal apodemes reaching 5th abdominal sternite. Pygofer side with process simple (
<figureCitation box="[1232,1309,1693,1718]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–39" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1268,1290]" captionTargetBox="[243,1369,365,1219]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[188,1398,339,1247]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 35–39. T. elongata sp. nov. 35, aedeagus, lateral view. 36, aedeagus and connective, posterior view. 37, paramere. 38, pygofer side, lateral view. 39. subgenital plate, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1455381/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="598">Fig.38</figureCitation>
). Paramere with subapical protrusion narrow and triangular (
<figureCitation box="[727,804,1729,1754]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–39" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1268,1290]" captionTargetBox="[243,1369,365,1219]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[188,1398,339,1247]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 35–39. T. elongata sp. nov. 35, aedeagus, lateral view. 36, aedeagus and connective, posterior view. 37, paramere. 38, pygofer side, lateral view. 39. subgenital plate, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1455381/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="598">Fig.37</figureCitation>
). Connective short and broad with apical feet slender (
<figureCitation box="[159,237,1765,1790]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–39" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1268,1290]" captionTargetBox="[243,1369,365,1219]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[188,1398,339,1247]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 35–39. T. elongata sp. nov. 35, aedeagus, lateral view. 36, aedeagus and connective, posterior view. 37, paramere. 38, pygofer side, lateral view. 39. subgenital plate, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1455381/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="598">Fig.36</figureCitation>
). Process of dorsal apodeme of aedeagus arched in lateral view with terminal hooks slender, Y-shaped in posterior view; aedeagal shafts broadened in lateral view with two widely separated tooth-like protrusions, one subapical and one at midlength, both directed ventrad (
<figureCitation box="[766,898,1837,1862]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–39" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1268,1290]" captionTargetBox="[243,1369,365,1219]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[188,1398,339,1247]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 35–39. T. elongata sp. nov. 35, aedeagus, lateral view. 36, aedeagus and connective, posterior view. 37, paramere. 38, pygofer side, lateral view. 39. subgenital plate, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1455381/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="598">Figs 35–36</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
