<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="599" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="599">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,223,248]" pageId="6" pageNumber="599">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin word “ 
<emphasis box="[994,1103,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="599">elongatus</emphasis>
” which means “elongated”, referring to its longer apical part of process of dorsal apodeme of aedeagus.
</paragraph>
